<TITLE> Bulu on trial for tax evasion </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 4 (bdnews24.com)A Dhaka court framed tax evasion charges against Jubo Dal president Barkatullah Bulu on Tuesday. Bulu, who was a former commerce adviser for the four-party alliance, is currently fugitive. Judge Yasmin Ara Begum of the Special Judge's Court-4 framed charges against Bulu in his absence and fixed Nov 9 to start hearing witnesses. Seven people have been named witnesses on behalf of the state. Assistant tax commissioner of the National Board of Revenue, Mortuza Shariful Islam, filed the case on Oct 19. The Jubo Dal chief is charged with dodging taxes of Tk 18.29 lakh, through concealment of Tk 70.99 lakh in undeclared earnings, during the tax years 2002-03 to 2006-07. bdnew
